description.en:
A series of thrilling urban dramas reveal the helplessness of city dwellers who have little control over their fate: "Burning Rage"—A man wronged by society, seeking self-preservation, acts as the city's judge, resorting to violence to solve all problems; "Death Hotline"—A phone call seeking a partner leads to deadly consequences; "No Way to Call for Help"—An extramarital affair that should never have happened results in the destruction of a family; "Planting Flowers"—A close friend who understands one's own heart turns out to be a killer who ruins one's life; "Sniper's Danger"—A dangerous love story between an undercover policeman and a nun; "Love and Murder"—An unusual relationship between two men leads to a series of murders, with the killer vowing to kill all homosexuals in the world. "Like a Dream"—The person you love and know best turns out to know nothing about you at all;

"Injustice"—A misunderstanding, an eyewitness's accusation, unfolds a story of injustice;

"A Treacherous Journey"—Two women from different social classes suffer the same misfortune because they mistakenly love the same man;

"The Horrifying Tale of Love"—Searching and searching, pursuing the love of their hearts, one wrong decision leads to a lifetime of regret.
